{"title_page": "Girithron", "text_new": "#REDIRECT [[N\u00famenor#Calendar]]\n\n{{R ME to section}}\n", "text_old": "#REDIRECT [[N\u00famenor#Calendar]]\n[[Category:Middle-earth redirects to sections]]\n", "name_user": "1234qwer1234qwer4", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:rcat template instead of cat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Girithron&redirect=no"}
{"title_page": "Tommy Diablo", "text_new": "{{short description|Puerto Rican professional wrestler}}\n{{Infobox professional wrestler\n|name=Tommy Diablo\n|birthname=Armando Gorbea\n|image=File:Tommy Diablo.jpg\n|names= '''Tommy Diablo'''\n|height= {{height|ft=5|in=8}}\n|weight= {{convert|200|lb|kg|abbr=on}}\n|birth_place =[[Carolina, Puerto Rico]]\n|trainer = Isaac Rosario\n|debut=2000\n|}}\n\n'''Armando Gorbea''', better known as '''Tommy Diablo''', is a professional wrestler better known for wrestling in both the [[International Wrestling Association (Puerto Rico)|International Wrestling Association]] in [[Puerto Rico]] and the [[World Wrestling Council]], where he is a fifteen-time [[WWC World Junior Heavyweight Championship|WWC World Junior Heavyweight Champion]].\n\n==Professional career==\n\n===Debut and International Wrestling Association (2000\u20132002)===\nIn 2000 Tommy Diablo made his professional debut in the [[International Wrestling Association (Puerto Rico)|International Wrestling Association]] of Puerto Rico. His first notable feud was aganist Andy Anderson and [[Tiger Ali Singh]], during this angle he teamed up with [[Steve Bradley]]. The feud was part of Club WWF a weekly television program transmitted on [[Telemundo]]. He spent a period of two years feuding with the Junior Heavyweight wrestlers as well as the company\u2019s young talent. During this time frame he would win his first professional championship, the [[IWA Junior Heavyweight Championship|IWA Junior Heavyweight Title]]. He held the title for one week before losing it against Paparazzi. He had feuds with Diab\u00f3lico, Anarchy, Paparazzi and [[Eric Perez|Eric Alexander]].\n\n===World Wrestling Council (2002\u20132003)===\nDiablo left the IWA and debuted on the [[World Wrestling Council]] during 2002. He was involved in a feud against [[Eddie Col\u00f3n]] over the WWC Junior Heavyweight championship. He would fail to acquire the title for Colon. When Colon was defeated in a title match against [[Kid Kash]], Diablo would develop a feud for the title. He won the WWC Junior Heavyweight championship on December 14, 2002. He won the title against Brent D\u00e1il in a match to determine a new champion after the title was vacated by Kash. He teamed with Wilfredo Alejandro in an angle where he would attempt to unmask a wrestler that was playing mind games with him. Tommy Diablo was part of ''La Invasion Dominicana'' a heel faction led by El Bronco and Chicky Starr.\n\n===International Wrestling Association (2003\u20132007)===\nDiablo would make a return to the International Wrestling Association in 2003. He was involved in an angle in which he helped Paparazzi in a feud with Stefano, this angle lasted through fall. On September 20, 2003 he won his second IWA Junior Heavyweight title by defeating Noriega. He had a feud with fellow cruiserweight wrestler Blitz, winning the title a third time from him. On October 30, 2004 he lost the title in a match against Golden Boy. He was involved in an angle in which he was (kayfabe) gravely injured by [[German Figueroa|Apolo]], he was out of action until early 2005. He was involved in a feud with Super Mark eventually defeating him for Junior Heavyweight title on May 21, 2005 in [[Toa Baja, Puerto Rico]]. He defended his title successfully against Carlito numerous times, and held it until Carlitos defeated him on October 1, 2005. He would have taken part in an angle involving several cruiserweight wrestler including Blitz, Carlitos and Hiram Tua. He is currently the leader of a stable of young heel superstars consisting of Super Mark, Cruzz and GQ the ravishing. He won the newly created IWA Cruiserweight championship by defeating Blitz on March 4, 2007 in Guanica, Puerto Rico.\n\n===World Wrestling Council (2008\u2013present)===\nTommy Diablo returned to WWC in 2008 and immediately he was involved in a feud with BJ. On August 9 he won the [[WWC Puerto Rico Heavyweight Championship]] after beating BJ thanks to his associate Aquiles. On December 13, at Lockout he lost the title against BJ in a ladder match. He later became a member of the heel group 'La familia 'with El Bronco, [[Steve Corino]], Charles Evans and other superstars.\n\nHe gained the [[WWC Junior Heavyweight Championship]] at February 27, 2010 by defeating Rikochet at the event Noche de Campeones.\n\nIn 2014 he won the [[WWC Junior Heavyweight Championship]] by defeating his former best friend [[Angel Fashion]] to become a 9 times champion. On September 7, 2014 at Septiembre Negro, Fashion defeated Diablo in a title match. Also, per the stipulations of the match, Diablo became a referee.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.prwrestling.com/nw/resultados-wwc-septiembre-negro-bayamon-96/|title=RESULTADOS WWC SEPTIEMBRE NEGRO BAYAMON 9/6|website=www.prwrestling.com}}</ref> On January 9, 2016, Diablo defeated Peter Romance to become an 11 times Junior Heavyweight champion.\n\n===AAA (2014)===\nOn August he traveled to Mexico promotion [[Lucha Libre AAA World Wide|AAA]] with El Sesancional Carlitos to enter a fatal 4 way eliminating for the [[AAA World Tag Team Championship|AAA World Tag Team Titles]] they fight till be the last 4 but been defeated by the current champions [[Ang\u00e9lico]] & [[Jack Evans (wrestler)|Jack Evans]]\n\n==Championships and accomplishments==\n*'''[[International Wrestling Association (Puerto Rico)|International Wrestling Association]]'''\n**[[IWA Hardcore Championship]] ([[IWA Hardcore Championship#Title history|3 times]]) <ref>{{cite web| title=Historia del Campeonato Hardcore| url=http://www.iwapr.tv/noticias/historiahardcore.php| language=Spanish| accessdate=2007-05-29 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070528142340/http://www.iwapr.tv/noticias/historiahardcore.php <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-05-28}}</ref>\n**[[IWA World Cruiserweight Championship|IWA Cruiserweight Championship]] ([[IWA World Cruiserweight Championship#Title History|1 time]])<ref>{{cite web| title=Historia del Campeonato Crusero Extremo| url=http://www.iwapr.tv/noticias/historiacruceroextremo.php| language=Spanish| accessdate=2007-05-29 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070615153025/http://www.iwapr.tv/noticias/historiacruceroextremo.php <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-06-15}}</ref>\n**[[IWA World Junior Heavyweight Championship|IWA Junior Heavyweight Championship]] ([[IWA World Junior Heavyweight Championship#Title history|6 times]])<ref>{{cite web| title=Historia del Campeonato Mundial Jr. Completo|url=http://www.iwapr.tv/noticias/historiamundialjr.php| language=Spanish| accessdate=2007-05-29 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070523080617/http://www.iwapr.tv/noticias/historiamundialjr.php <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-05-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cagematch.net//?id=5&nr=259|title=IWA Puerto Rico Junior Heavyweight Championship \u00ab Titles Database \u00ab CAGEMATCH - The Internet Wrestling Database|website=www.cagematch.net}}</ref>\n*'''Lucha Xtrema Nacional de Panam\u00e1'''\n**LXN Tag Team Championship (2 times) - with [[Juventud Guerrera]]<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://superluchas.net/2009/11/22/resultados-lxn-noviembre-nuclear-20-noviembre-2009-juventud-guerrera-y-tommy-diablo-pierden-sus-titulos/ |title=Resultados LXN Noviembre Nuclear (20 Noviembre 2009) - Juventud Guerrera y Tommy Diablo pierden sus t\u00edtulos |author=Randall Gord\u00f3n |magazine=Super Luchas |language=Spanish |date=2009-11-22 |accessdate=2012-08-20}}</ref> and Gran Tonka\n*'''[[World Wrestling Council]]'''\n**[[WWC World Junior Heavyweight Championship]] ([[WWC World Junior Heavyweight Championship#Title history|16 times]])<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.wrestling-titles.com/us/pr/wwc/wwc-j.html| title=World Wrestling Council: World Junior Heavyweight Title| accessdate=2007-05-29| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20070522154929/http://www.wrestling-titles.com/us/pr/wwc/wwc-j.html| archivedate= 22 May 2007 | url-status= live}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=http://wrestlingdata.com/index.php?befehl=bios&wrestler=2995&bild=1&details=3|title=Wrestlingdata.com - The World's Largest Wrestling Database|website=wrestlingdata.com}}</ref>\n**[[WWC Puerto Rico Championship]] ([[WWC Puerto Rico Championship#Title history|1 time]])<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n**[[WWC World Tag Team Championship]] ([[WWC World Tag Team Championship#Title history|2 times]]) - with Johnny Ringo (1) and Cuervo (1) <ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Professional wrestling in Puerto Rico]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Diablo, Tommy}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Carolina, Puerto Rico]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican male professional wrestlers]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Puerto Rican professional wrestler}}\n{{Infobox professional wrestler\n|name=Tommy Diablo\n|birthname=Armando Gorbea\n|image=File:Tommy Diablo.jpg\n|names= '''Tommy Diablo'''\n|height= {{height|ft=5|in=8}}\n|weight= {{convert|200|lb|kg|abbr=on}}\n|birth_place =[[Carolina, Puerto Rico]]\n|trainer = Isaac Rosario\n|debut=2000\n|}}\n\n'''Armando Gorbea''', better known as '''Tommy Diablo''', is a professional wrestler better known for wrestling in both the [[International Wrestling Association (Puerto Rico)|International Wrestling Association]] in [[Puerto Rico]] and the [[World Wrestling Council]], where he is an fifteen-time [[WWC World Junior Heavyweight Championship|WWC World Junior Heavyweight Champion]].\n\n==Professional career==\n\n===Debut and International Wrestling Association (2000-2002)===\nIn 2000 Tommy Diablo made his professional debut in the [[International Wrestling Association (Puerto Rico)|International Wrestling Association]] of Puerto Rico. His first notable feud was a ganist Andy Anderson and [[Tiger Ali Singh]], during this angle he teamed up with [[Steve Bradley]]. The feud was part of Club WWF a weekly television program transmitted on [[Telemundo]]. He spent a period of two years feuding with the Junior Heavyweight wrestlers as well as the company\u2019s young talent. During this time frame he would win his first professional championship, the [[IWA Junior Heavyweight Championship|IWA Junior Heavyweight Title]]. He held the title for one week before losing it against Paparazzi. He had feuds with Diab\u00f3lico, Anarchy, Paparazzi and [[Eric Perez|Eric Alexander]].\n\n===World Wrestling Council (2002 - 2003)===\nDiablo left the IWA and debuted on the [[World Wrestling Council]] during 2002. He was involved in a feud against [[Eddie Col\u00f3n]] over the WWC Junior Heavyweight championship. He would fail to acquire the title for Colon. When Colon was defeated in a title match against [[Kid Kash]], Diablo would develop a feud for the title. He won the WWC Junior Heavyweight championship on December 14, 2002. He won the title against Brent D\u00e1il in a match to determine a new champion after the title was vacated by Kash. He teamed with Wilfredo Alejandro in an angle where he would attempt to unmask a wrestler that was playing mind games with him. Tommy Diablo was part of ''La Invasion Dominicana'' a heel faction led by El Bronco and Chicky Starr.\n\n===International Wrestling Association (2003-2007)===\nDiablo would make a return to the International Wrestling Association in 2003. He was involved in an angle in which he helped Paparazzi in a feud with Stefano, this angle lasted though fall. On September 20, 2003 he won his second IWA Junior Heavyweight title by defeating Noriega. He had a feud with fellow cruiserweight wrestler Blitz, winning the title a third time from him. On October 30, 2004 he lost the title in a match against Golden Boy. He was involved in an angle in which he was (kayfabe) gravely injured by [[German Figueroa|Apolo]], he was out of action until early 2005. He was involved in a feud with Super Mark eventually defeating him for Junior Heavyweight title on May 21, 2005 in [[Toa Baja, Puerto Rico]]. He defended his title successfully against Carlito numerous times, and held it until Carlitos defeated him on October 1, 2005. He would have taken part in an angle involving several cruiserweight wrestler including Blitz, Carlitos and Hiram Tua. He is currently the leader of a stable of young heel superstars consisting of Super Mark, Cruzz ang GQ the ravishing. He won the newly created IWA Cruiserweight championship by defeating Blitz on March 4, 2007 in Guanica, Puerto Rico.\n\n===World Wrestling Council (2008-present)===\nTommy Diablo returned to WWC in 2008 and immediately he was involved in feud with BJ. On August 9 he win the [[WWC Puerto Rico Heavyweight Championship]] after beating BJ thanks to his associate Aquiles. On December 13, at Lockout he lost the title against BJ in a ladder match. He later became a member of the heel group 'La familia 'with El Bronco, [[Steve Corino]], Charles Evans and other superstars.\n\nHe gain the [[WWC Junior Heavyweight Championship]] at February 27, 2010 by defeating Rikochet at the event Noche de Campeones.\n\nIn 2014 he won the [[WWC Junior Heavyweight Championship]] by defeating his former best friend [[Angel Fashion]] to become a 9 times champion. On September 7, 2014 at Septiembre Negro, Fashion defeated Diablo in a title match. Also, per the stipulations of the match, Diablo became a referee.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.prwrestling.com/nw/resultados-wwc-septiembre-negro-bayamon-96/|title=RESULTADOS WWC SEPTIEMBRE NEGRO BAYAMON 9/6|website=www.prwrestling.com}}</ref> On January 9, 2016, Diablo defeated Peter Romance to become an 11 times Junior Heavyweight champion.\n\n===AAA (2014)===\nOn August he traveled to Mexico promotion [[Lucha Libre AAA World Wide|AAA]] with El Sesancional Carlitos to enter a fatal 4 way eliminating for the [[AAA World Tag Team Championship|AAA World Tag Team Titles]] they fight till be the last 4 but been defeated by the current champions [[Ang\u00e9lico]] & [[Jack Evans (wrestler)|Jack Evans]]\n\n==Championships and accomplishments==\n*'''[[International Wrestling Association (Puerto Rico)|International Wrestling Association]]'''\n**[[IWA Hardcore Championship]] ([[IWA Hardcore Championship#Title history|3 times]]) <ref>{{cite web| title=Historia del Campeonato Hardcore| url=http://www.iwapr.tv/noticias/historiahardcore.php| language=Spanish| accessdate=2007-05-29 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070528142340/http://www.iwapr.tv/noticias/historiahardcore.php <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-05-28}}</ref>\n**[[IWA World Cruiserweight Championship|IWA Cruiserweight Championship]] ([[IWA World Cruiserweight Championship#Title History|1 time]])<ref>{{cite web| title=Historia del Campeonato Crusero Extremo| url=http://www.iwapr.tv/noticias/historiacruceroextremo.php| language=Spanish| accessdate=2007-05-29 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070615153025/http://www.iwapr.tv/noticias/historiacruceroextremo.php <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-06-15}}</ref>\n**[[IWA World Junior Heavyweight Championship|IWA Junior Heavyweight Championship]] ([[IWA World Junior Heavyweight Championship#Title history|6 times]])<ref>{{cite web| title=Historia del Campeonato Mundial Jr. Completo|url=http://www.iwapr.tv/noticias/historiamundialjr.php| language=Spanish| accessdate=2007-05-29 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070523080617/http://www.iwapr.tv/noticias/historiamundialjr.php <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-05-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cagematch.net//?id=5&nr=259|title=IWA Puerto Rico Junior Heavyweight Championship \u00ab Titles Database \u00ab CAGEMATCH - The Internet Wrestling Database|website=www.cagematch.net}}</ref>\n*'''Lucha Xtrema Nacional de Panam\u00e1'''\n**LXN Tag Team Championship (2 times) - with [[Juventud Guerrera]]<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://superluchas.net/2009/11/22/resultados-lxn-noviembre-nuclear-20-noviembre-2009-juventud-guerrera-y-tommy-diablo-pierden-sus-titulos/ |title=Resultados LXN Noviembre Nuclear (20 Noviembre 2009) - Juventud Guerrera y Tommy Diablo pierden sus t\u00edtulos |author=Randall Gord\u00f3n |magazine=Super Luchas |language=Spanish |date=2009-11-22 |accessdate=2012-08-20}}</ref> and Gran Tonka\n*'''[[World Wrestling Council]]'''\n**[[WWC World Junior Heavyweight Championship]] ([[WWC World Junior Heavyweight Championship#Title history|16 times]])<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.wrestling-titles.com/us/pr/wwc/wwc-j.html| title=World Wrestling Council: World Junior Heavyweight Title| accessdate=2007-05-29| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20070522154929/http://www.wrestling-titles.com/us/pr/wwc/wwc-j.html| archivedate= 22 May 2007 | url-status= live}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=http://wrestlingdata.com/index.php?befehl=bios&wrestler=2995&bild=1&details=3|title=Wrestlingdata.com - The World's Largest Wrestling Database|website=wrestlingdata.com}}</ref>\n**[[WWC Puerto Rico Championship]] ([[WWC Puerto Rico Championship#Title history|1 time]])<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n**[[WWC World Tag Team Championship]] ([[WWC World Tag Team Championship#Title history|2 times]]) - with Johnny Ringo (1) and Cuervo (1) <ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Professional wrestling in Puerto Rico]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Diablo, Tommy}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Carolina, Puerto Rico]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican male professional wrestlers]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "name_user": "LilHelpa", "label": "safe", "comment": "copy edit", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tommy_Diablo"}
