be Sundial, Marine Walk, Swansea, Wales.JPG|200px]]\n|Globe [[Sundial]] sculpture\n|Marine Walk, [[Maritime Quarter]], [[Swansea]]\n|1987\n|[[Wendy Taylor]]\n|<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20160303224313/http://www.pmsa.org.uk/pmsa-database/11612/ Public Monument and Sculpture Association: Globe Sundial] Accessed 7 Sep 2017</ref>\n|{{coord|51|36|50.2|N|3|56|25.5|W}}\n\n|-\n|[[File:Lighthouse Sculpture, Swansea Waterfront.jpg|200px]]\n|Lighthouse Tower sculpture\n|Marine Walk, [[Maritime Quarter]], [[Swansea]]\n|1987\n|Robert Conybear\n|<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20160514025929/http://pmsa.org.uk/pmsa-database/11613/ Public Monument and Sculpture Association: Lighthouse Tower sculpture] Accessed 7 Sep 2017</ref><ref name=\"AStace\"/>\n|{{coord|51|36|51|N|3|56|19.9|W}}\n|-\n|[[File:Helwick lightship wall sculpture, Swansea, Wales.jpg|200px]]\n|Helwick [[Lightvessel|Lightship]]. One of four wall sculptures featuring nautical history.\n|Marine Walk, walkway to Ocean Crescent, [[Maritime Quarter]], [[Swansea]]\n|c1985-1990\n|Robin Campbell (designer), Philip Chatfield (sculptor)\n|see below\n|{{coord|51|36|50.76|N|3|56|25.7|W|region:GB}}\n|-\n|[[File:Zeta Wall Sculpture, Ocean Crescent, Swansea.JPG|200px]]\n|The copper ore [[barque]], Zeta. One of four wall sculptures featuring nautical history.\n|Marine Walk, walkway to Ocean Crescent, [[Maritime Quarter]], [[Swansea]]\n|c1985-1990\n|Robin Campbell (designer), Philip Chatfield (sculptor)\n|<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20160303222202/http://www.pmsa.org.uk/pmsa-database/11854/ Public Monument and Sculpture Association: Zeta Wall Sculpture] Accessed 7 Sep 2017</ref>\n|{{coord|51|36|51.6|N|3|56|19.4|W}}\n|-\n|[[File:Boatshed Doors, Marine Walk, Swansea.JPG|200px]]\n|The Boatshed Doors\n|Marine Walk, close to the [[Marina Towers Observatory]]\n|c1985-1990\n|Robert Conybear, Robin Campbell\n|<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20160304002503/http://www.pmsa.org.uk/pmsa-database/11850/ Public Monument and Sculpture Association: Boatshed Doors] Accessed 7 Sep 2017</ref>\n|{{coord|51|36|51.5|N|3|56|10.8|W}}\n|-\n|[[File:Ecliptica Weather Vane, Swansea Observatory.jpg|200px]]\n|'Ecliptica' sculpture and [[weather vane]], [[Marina Towers Observatory]]\n|Sea promenade, [[Maritime Quarter]], [[Swansea]]\n|1989 (building), 1991 (sculpture)\n|Robin Campbell (architect),  Robert Conybear, Uta Molling (sculptors \u2013 'Ecliptica' weather vane)\n|<ref>[http://www.explore-gower.co.uk/explore/swansea/marina-towers Explore Gower: Marina Towers Observatory] Accessed 7 Sep 2017</ref><ref>[https://www.google.com/search?tbm=bks&hl=en&q=swansea+observatory+sculpture&btnG= Google Books:  Observatory Weather Vane] Accessed 7 Sep 2017</ref><ref name=\"AStace\">{{cite book|author=Alison Stace|publisher=Herbert Press|year=2017|title= Sculpture Parks and Trails of Great Britain and Ireland (Second Edition) |ISBN=978 1 912217 25 0}}</ref>\n|{{coord|51|36|50.4|N|3|56|12|W}}\n|-\n|[[File:Sculptures, Marina Towers Observatory, Swansea, Wales.JPG|200px]]\n|Sculptures on the [[Marina Towers Observatory]]\n|Sea promenade, [[Maritime Quarter]], [[Swansea]]\n|1989 (building)\n|Robin Campbell (architect)  \n| \n|{{coord|51|36|50.61|N|3|56|12.99|W|region:GB}}\n|-\n|[[File:The Mermaid, Swansea, Wales.JPG|200px]]\n|The [[Mermaid]]\n|Marine Walk, [[Maritime Quarter]], [[Swansea]]\n|1989\n|Gordon Young\n|<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20160303214532/http://www.pmsa.org.uk/pmsa-database/11611/ Public Monument and Sculpture Association: The Mermaid] Accessed 7 Sep 2017</ref><ref name=\"AStace\"/>\n|{{coord|51|36|50.8|N|3|56|13.9|W}}\n|-\n|[[File:Spolasco, Swansea.JPG|200px]][[File:Spolasco 2, Patagonia Walk, Swansea.JPG|200px]]\n|'Baron' Spolasco, a [[quackery|quack]] doctor who lived in Swansea in the 1830s\n|Patagonia Walk, just off Trawler Road, [[Maritime Quarter]], [[Swansea]]\n|c1985-1990\n|Robin Campbell, Richard Porch (designers), [[Jonah Jones (sculptor)|Jonah Jones]], Meic Watts, Brian Denman (sculptors)\n|<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20160514025947/http://pmsa.org.uk/pmsa-database/11852/ Public Monument and Sculpture Association: Spolasco] Accessed 7 Sep 2017</ref>\n|{{coord|51|36|53.5|N|3|56|20.3|W}}\n|-\n|[[File:Captain Cat.jpg|200px]]\n|Captain Cat from [[Under Milk Wood]] by [[Dylan Thomas]]\n|Abernethy Quay, [[Maritime Quarter]], [[Swansea]]\n|1990\n| Robert J R Thomas (sculptor)\n|<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20160304000830/http://www.pmsa.org.uk/pmsa-database/11458/ Public Monument and Sculpture Association: Captain Cat] Accessed 7 Sep 2017</ref>\n|{{coord|51|36|59.1|N|3|56|9.5|W}}\n|-\n|[[File:Turbo, Pharos wall design, Swansea.jpg|200px]]\n|Turbo Pharos wall sculpture\n|[[Maritime Quarter]], [[Swansea]]\n|\n| \n|\n|\n|-\n|[[File:Mannheim Quay wall design, Swansea.jpg|200px]]\n|Mannheim Quay wall sculpture\n|[[Maritime Quarter]], [[Swansea]]\n|\n| \n|\n|{{Location|51|37|2.4|N|3|56|6.7|W}}\n|-\n|[[File:Pumphouse Quay, Maritime Quarter, Swansea.jpg|200px]]\n|Pumphouse Quay wall sculpture\n|Next to the Pump House, [[Maritime Quarter]], [[Swansea]]\n|\n| \n|\n|{{coord|51|37|0|N|3|56|10.3|W}}\n|-\n|[[File:Dylan Thomas, Maritime Quarter, Swansea.JPG|200px]]\n|[[Dylan Thomas]]\n| Dylan Thomas Square, [[Maritime Quarter]], [[Swansea]]\n|1984\n| [[John Doubleday]]\n|<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20160303215634/http://www.pmsa.org.uk/pmsa-database/11466/ Public Monument and Sculpture Association: Dylan Thomas] Accessed 7 Sep 2017</ref>\n|{{coord|51|36|59.8|N|3|56|14|W}}\n|-\n|[[File:Mural, Dylan Thomas Theatre, Swansea, Wales.JPG|200px]]\n|[[Dylan Thomas Theatre]] wall sculpture and [[mural]]\n|West wall of Theatre, Dylan Thomas Square, [[Maritime Quarter]], [[Swansea]]\n|c1979\n| \n|(see below)\n|{{coord|51|37|0.5|N|3|56|16.27|W|region:GB}}\n|-\n|[[File:Dylan Thomas Theatre, Swansea - geograph.org.uk - 220927.jpg|200px]]\n|[[Dylan Thomas Theatre]] [[mural]], depicting scenes from [[Dylan Thomas]]'s life.\n|Dylan Thomas Square, [[Maritime Quarter]]