05\n|Philip Chatfield\n|<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/wales/4623883.stm BBC Wales: Merchant Navy Memorial] Accessed 7 Sep 2017</ref><ref>[http://www3.swansea.gov.uk/cmsr/presssystem/PressReleaseTemplate2.asp?starget=/cmsr/presssystem/pressdata/2003/20031217memorial%20for%20merchant%20navy%20in%20swansea.htm&DocTitle=Memorial%20for%20Merchant%20Navy%20in%20Swansea City and County of Swansea Press Release: Merchant Navy Memorial] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110930034400/http://www3.swansea.gov.uk/cmsr/presssystem/PressReleaseTemplate2.asp?starget=%2Fcmsr%2Fpresssystem%2Fpressdata%2F2003%2F20031217memorial%20for%20merchant%20navy%20in%20swansea.htm&DocTitle=Memorial%20for%20Merchant%20Navy%20in%20Swansea |date=30 September 2011 }} Accessed 7 Sep 2017</ref>\n|{{coord|51|37|13.4|N|3|55|54.7|W}}\n|-\n|[[File:Riverside sculpture Swansea.JPG|200px]]\n|Riverside sculpture \n|By River Tawe, outside Sainsbury's, [[SA1 Swansea Waterfront]]\n|\n|\n|\n|{{coord|51|37|11.9|N|3|56|3.9|W}}\n|-\n|[[File:Flying Figurehead, Swansea, Wales.JPG|200px]]\n|Flying [[Figurehead (object)|Figurehead]]\n|Quay Parade, near Sainsbury's, [[SA1 Swansea Waterfront]]\n|1988\n|David Backhouse\n|<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20160303221050/http://www.pmsa.org.uk/pmsa-database/11456/ Public Monument and Sculpture Association: Flying Figurehead] Accessed 7 Sep 2017{{deadlink|date=March 2019}}</ref>\n|{{coord|51|37|17.62|N|3|56|8.72|W|region:GB}}\n|-\n|[[File:Sculpture, Trawler Road, Swansea.JPG|200px]]\n|Light Wave\n|Crescent Park, [[Swansea Point]], [[Swansea]]\n|2009\n|Peter Freeman\n|\n|{{coord|51|36|54.7|N|3|55|58.3|W}}\n|-\n|[[File:Acoustic Sculpture 2, Swansea Point, Swansea.JPG|200px]]\n|Acoustic Sculpture 1\n|[[Swansea Point]], [[Swansea]]\n|2009\n|Rob Olins\n| <ref name=\"AStace\"/>\n|{{coord|51|36|53.28|N|3|55|58.25|W|region:GB}}\n|-\n|[[File:Acoustic sculpture, Swansea Point, Swansea.JPG|200px]]\n|Acoustic Sculpture 2\n|[[Swansea Point]], [[Swansea]]\n|2009\n|Rob Olins