{"title_page": "2019\u201320 Basketball Championship of Bosnia and Herzegovina", "text_new": "{{Infobox basketball league season|updated=|prevseason=[[2018\u201319 Basketball Championship of Bosnia and Herzegovina|2018\u201319]]|nextseason=[[2020\u201321 Basketball Championship of Bosnia and Herzegovina|2020\u201321]]|title=Prvenstvo BiH|t_bg=#161796; color:white; border:2px solid #FFCD00;|t_color=|image=|caption=|champions=[[KK Igokea|Igokea]]|runners_up=|third_place=|fourth_place=|promoted=|relegated=|teams=12|games=|duration=October 2019 \u2013 May 2020|top_seed=|MVP=|finals_MVP=|final_four_MVP=|top_scorer=|ppg=18.5|rebounds_leader=|rpg=11.3|assists_leader=|apg=6.3|highest_scoring=|winning_streak=|losing_streak=|biggest_home_win=|biggest_away_win=|highest_attendance=|lowest_attendance=|average_attendance=|season=2019\u201320|pixels=90px|semifinalists=}}\n\nThe '''2019\u201320 Basketball Championship of Bosnia and Herzegovina''' was the 19th season of [[Basketball Championship of Bosnia and Herzegovina|this championship]], with 12 teams from Bosnia and Herzegovina participating in it. [[HKK \u0160iroki]] were the defending champion. On 13 March 2020, season was ended prematurely because of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]], naming [[KK Igokea|Igokea]] as new champion.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://basket.ba/saopstenje-za-javnost-2/|publisher=Basketball Federation of BiH|date=16 March 2020|title=Saop\u0161tenje za javnost}}</ref>\n\n\n== Competition format ==\nTwelve teams would join the regular season, played with as double round-robin tournament. [[KK Igokea|Igokea]] joined the competition, although they declined to participate previous season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://basketball.hr/vijesti/igokea-se-vraca-u-prvenstvo-bih-kao-da-nista-nije-bilo/8412|title=Igokea se vra\u0107a u Prvenstvo BiH-a kao da ni\u0161ta nije bilo|website=Basketball.hr|language=hr|access-date=2019-08-28}}</ref>\n\n== Teams and locations ==\n{{location map+|Bosnia and Herzegovina|width=400|float=right|caption=Locations of the '''2019\u201320 Basketball Championship of Bosnia and Herzegovina''' teams|places={{location map~ |Bosnia and Herzegovina |lat=43.866667 |long=18.416667 |label=[[OKK Spars Sarajevo|Spars]]}}\n{{Location map~ |Bosnia and Herzegovina |lat=44.182961 |long=19.333292 |label=[[KK Bratunac|Bratunac]]|position=left}}\n{{Location map~ |Bosnia and Herzegovina |lat=44.131111 |long=18.097222 |label=[[KK Kakanj|Kakanj]]|position=top}}\n{{Location map~ |Bosnia and Herzegovina |lat=44.909167 |long=17.301667 |label=[[KK Igokea|Igokea]]|position=top}}\n{{Location map~ |Bosnia and Herzegovina |lat=44.15 |long=17.4 |label=[[KK Promo Donji Vakuf|Promo]]|position=top}}\n{{Location map~ |Bosnia and Herzegovina |lat=42.712 |long=18.346 |label=[[KK Leotar|Leotar]]|position=top}}\n{{Location map~ |Bosnia and Herzegovina |lat=43.111828 |long=17.705483 |label=[[HKK \u010capljina Lasta|\u010capljina Lasta]]|position=right}}\n{{location map~ |Bosnia and Herzegovina |lat=44.416667 |long=17.083333 |label=[[KK Mladost Mrkonji\u0107 Grad|Mladost]]|position=left}}\n{{location map~ |Bosnia and Herzegovina |lat=44.538056 |long=18.676111 |label=[[OKK Sloboda Tuzla|Sloboda]]|position=left}}\n{{location map~ |Bosnia and Herzegovina |lat=43.383142 |long=17.592739 |label=[[HKK \u0160iroki|\u0160iroki]]|position=top}}\n{{location map~ |Bosnia and Herzegovina |lat=43.9      |long=18.35     |label=[[KK Vogo\u0161\u0107a|Vogo\u0161\u0107a]]|position=top}}\n{{location map~ |Bosnia and Herzegovina |lat=43.333333 |long=17.8      |label=[[HKK Zrinjski Mostar|Zrinjski]]|position=right}}}}\n[[HKK \u010capljina Lasta|\u010capljina Lasta]], [[KK Leotar|Leotar]] and [[KK Donji Vakuf|Promo]] were promoted from the previous season.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Team\n!City\n!Venue\n|-\n|[[KK Bratunac|Bratunac]]\n|[[Bratunac]]\n|SD Bratunac\n|-\n|[[HKK \u010capljina Lasta|\u010capljina Lasta]]\n|[[\u010capljina]]\n|\u0160portska dvorana \u010capljina\n|