ory:2019\u201320 in Bosnia and Herzegovina basketball|Bas]]\n[[Category:Current basketball seasons|Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox basketball league season|updated=|prevseason=[[2018\u201319 Basketball Championship of Bosnia and Herzegovina|2018\u201319]]|nextseason=[[2020\u201321 Basketball Championship of Bosnia and Herzegovina|2020\u201321]]|title=Prvenstvo BiH|t_bg=#161796; color:white; border:2px solid #FFCD00;|t_color=|image=|caption=|champions=[[KK Igokea|Igokea]]|runners_up=|third_place=|fourth_place=|promoted=|relegated=|teams=12|games=|duration=October 2019 \u2013 May 2020|top_seed=|MVP=|finals_MVP=|final_four_MVP=|top_scorer=|ppg=18.5|rebounds_leader=|rpg=11.3|assists_leader=|apg=6.3|highest_scoring=|winning_streak=|losing_streak=|biggest_home_win=|biggest_away_win=|highest_attendance=|lowest_attendance=|average_attendance=|season=2019\u201320|pixels=90px|semifinalists=}}\n\nThe '''2019\u201320 Basketball Championship of Bosnia and Herzegovina''' was the 19th season of [[Basketball Championship of Bosnia and Herzegovina|this championship]], with 12 teams from Bosnia and Herzegovina participating in it. [[HKK \u0160iroki]] were the defending champion. On 13 March 2020, season was ended prematurely because of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coranavirus pandemic]], naming [[KK Igokea|Igokea]] as new champion.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://basket.ba/saopstenje-za-javnost-2/|publisher=Basketball Federation of BiH|date=16 March 2020|title=Saop\u0161tenje za javnost}}</ref>\n\n\n== Competition format ==\nTwelve teams would join the regular season, played with as double round-robin tournament. [[KK Igokea|Igokea]] joined the competition, although they declined to participate previous season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://basketball.hr/vijesti/igokea-se-vraca-u-prvenstvo-bih-kao-da-nista-nije-bilo/8412|title=Igokea se vra\u0107a u Prvenstvo BiH-a kao da ni\u0161ta nije bilo|website=Basketball.hr|language=hr|access-date=2019-08-28}}</ref>\n\n=